TI  - SOCIAL REPRESENTATIONS AND DYNAMICS neighborhood in segregated areas CITY OF CORDOBA. THE ROLE OF PUBLIC POLICY IN THESE PROCESSES
T2  - SCRIPTA NOVA-REVISTA ELECTRONICA DE GEOGRAFIA Y CIENCIAS SOCIALES
KW  - socio-economic residential segregation
KW  - representations
KW  - neighborhood dynamics
KW  - social space built
AB  - The spatial clustering of households with similar socio-economic attributes and cultural segregation refers to the socio-economic residential if it is the creation of urban residential areas very homogeneous in terms of these characteristics and with some degree of heterogeneity in other areas surrounding. If this setting socio-spatial dynamics are characterized by marked neighborhood distinctions among people with limited interaction spaces are plural in the presence of segregation phenomenon.
   The poverty segregated spaces escazas plural relationships are likely to shrinking the circle of job opportunities, educational and socio-cultural circles of poverty generating gradual impoverishment of the community and social capital. These dynamics are based on neighborhood social representations "individual or collective symbolic constructions that subjects create to interpret the world, reflect on their own situation and that of others ..." (Vasilachis, 2003)
   The formulation and analysis of public policy generally does not address this dimension of analysis specifically exist in many cases the deepening of segregation phenomena from certain public actions.
